FlexoConcept.name: FunctionalGoal
FlexoConcept.description: A functional goal. This concept implements here many notions of the model. When no responsability is defined, this is a normal goal, to be refined. When a responsability is defined: - this is an Expectation if the responsability references an EnvironmentalAgent - this is a Requirement if the responsability references a SoftwareAgent

FlexoConceptInstanceRole.name: assignments
FlexoConceptInstanceRole.description: Assignment is used when several agents may be made responsible for some requirement or expectation.

FlexoConcept.name: Refinement
FlexoConcept.description: Defines a refinment relationship between a Goal and a collection of Goals Goals should be compatible (a functional requirement cannot emerge from a non functional requirement for example) Semantics of refinment is defined by sub-classes

FlexoConceptInstanceRole.name: childGoals
FlexoConceptInstanceRole.description: Collection of goals that define the refinment

FlexoConcept.name: Goal
FlexoConcept.description: An abstract Goal. Might be a functional or non-functional goal. A Goal might be achived by one of its defined refinments

FlexoConcept.name: NonFunctionalGoal
FlexoConcept.description: A non functional goal. This concept implements here many notions of the model. When no contributions are defined, this is a normal goal, to be refined. When at least one contribution is defined, this is an Elementary NonFunctionalGoal
